intro: Cryptocarya impressivena, commonly known as the impressivena cryptocarya, is a species of flowering plant in the family Lauraceae. It is native to New Zealand and is characterized by its evergreen leaves and small, fragrant flowers. The plant typically grows as a shrub or small tree, reaching heights of up to 5 meters. Its leaves are glossy and have a distinctive, intricate venation pattern. The fruit is a small, dark blue drupe that develops from the flower.
